_sText: Another user requested that I upload an all-pink version of my map, de_tvj_snowflakes, so here it is!
This map is a neon version of a slightly modified fy_iceworld_bunkers made by request.  Supports 24 players.

First map I've made in a LOOOOOONG time, so I started with a remake of a fairly simple layout which grew and evolved over the course of its creation. 
Generally fast paced gameplay, but it also includes a bomb site for when things need to move along.  I also chose to drop the scattered weapons at each spawn in favor of Buy Zones. 27 spawn points per team.  Enjoy!

DE_TV-TOWER

Remake of the tv-tower map from 1.6.



KNOWN PROBLEMS
---

*Displacement that leads into water near Terrorist spawn flickers black. I've tried everything I've thought of... doesn't help.

*Bots have trouble on this map. I edited nav file in the beta version ... but they still didn't work well. Did not include .nav file with this release because it would be pointless and use more space.



SIMILARITIES / DIFFERENCES TO 1.6 VERSION
---

*Sliding door on top of ladder still there.

*Elevator doors still there, but there's a button inside the lift to open and close them as well.

*Can't enter roof of tower.

*Is defusal instead of hostage rescue (cause of bad bot navigation).

*Has darker elevator than original.

*Elevator can be entered through an emergency exit.


MISC
---

*18 seconds to compile with HDR enabled.

*Around 11 cubemaps.

*2 custom "textures." 1 edited standard texture cause of the envmap bug (works perfect now).

*Don't rename the map otherwise cubemaps will stop working. Rename it if you want overly shiny HDR and shiny, glossy fingernails and weapons.

*Nothing was taken from the other remake, link: http://www.fpsbanana.com/maps/12773

*Many thanks to nay0r for noting improvements that should've been made.

===================================================================================
Map Information:
===================================================================================

Title:
de_turk

August 19, 2010

Authors:
Ryan Jones "Super Pie"

Version:
1.0

Email:
legendarysuperpie [at] gmail.com (Ryan Jones)

Website:
tankdragon.blogspot.com

Description:
It is a defusion bay map with some buildings. Pathways with objects to hide 
behind. Some reasonable sniping points. Orange. :)

Story:
Terrorists are trying to settle the score with "Big Money" of the area. They plan 
to bomb at least one of their two buildings. Destroying either of these buildings 
will greatly cripple them financially. "Big Money" found out about the Terrorists' 
plan and setup some security in the area. The Terrorists grouped up and prepared 
for their assault. This is where your choices make the difference. Will the 
Terrorists succeed or fail?

Side note:
This is my first map. Finally, after years, I finally completed a map for 
CS: Source! :D

===================================================================================
Installation:
===================================================================================

Just place the *.bsp file into your 
"$SteamUserDir\counter-strike source\cstrike\maps\" directory and go have some 
fun! :)

===================================================================================
Special Thanks to:
===================================================================================

3kliksphilip for the tutorials on his website/youtube.
rocketrascal34 (TopHATTwaffle) for the tutorials on his website/youtube.
...and to all the other random tutorials I have found over the web.
...and all the authors to the programs to make these maps possible [with ease].

...and you for downloading this map! :D

===================================================================================
Easter Egg(s):
===================================================================================

There is 1 turtle in this level.

===================================================================================
Problems?:
===================================================================================

If you see any problems with the map, either visually or with the gameplay, LET ME 
KNOW!

I plan on taking the information from people to make better maps for the 
community. :)

===================================================================================
Copyright:
===================================================================================

de_turk © Ryan Jones "Super Pie" 2010

I've made a lot of maps but this is the first map i've made that i've considered good enough to put online!

It can play fast or slow depending on the style of playing as there are fast routes and stealthy routes as well as sniper spots around the outside.

The Screenshots are of an older version!

IMPROVEMENTS

HDR, sun's position corresponds with lighting, more hiding places for the Terrorists, more furniture inside the castle and multiple different textures.

INSTRUCTIONS FOR THE COUNTER TERRORISTS

As Counter Terrorist your purpose is to either protect the bomb site located on top of the castle by killing all of the terrorists or to defuse the bomb once it has been placed.

INSTRUCTIONS FOR THE TERRORISTS

As Terrorist your purpose is to either kill every Counter Terrorist on the enemy team or to place and protect the bomb on top of the castle. There are 3 different ways into the castle:
         1. Deathride located in the head of the Trojan Horse.
         2. Cross the toxic river on the sides by jumping over the spheres.  Then use the ladders to climb on top of the castle.
         3. Simply enter the castle through the front door.

CREDITS

I'd like to thank High Voltage and Elise Cookie for testing the map and giving me inspiration. Secondly my thanks go to all of the YouTube users who uploaded some interesting tutorial videos about Hammer.

The following members deserve credit for the use of their work:

1. 1NzT4nT - Sand brick texture
2. kAR1SMA - Sand brick texture
